This paper deals with machine learning models and privacy preservation, which are both topics that fall under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the creation of a distributed system for privacy preservation, which could also fall under the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The use of a Variational Autoencoder (VAE) and Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) also suggests that the paper could be relevant to the sub-categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's emphasis on customization and individual preferences could also make it relevant to the sub-category of "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI).
